00","1010–Female":"1010.–preminula","0993–Female":"0993–preminula","993":"0993.","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010.","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italija"},"cs":{"993–":"0993–Zesnulá","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Zesnulá","0993–Female":"0993–Zesnulá","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Itálie"},"da":{"993–":"0993–Afdød","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Afdød","0993–Female":"0993–Afdød","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italien"},"nl":{"993–":"0993–Overleden","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Overleden","0993–Female":"0993–Overleden","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italië"},"en":{"993–":"0993–Deceased","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Deceased","0993–Female":"0993–Deceased","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italy","nameMeanings":[{"name":"di","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese:","Mandarin form of the surname 狄, a term referring to the tribes in ancient northern China: (i) from Di (狄), the name of an ancient state (thought to have been located in Hebei or Shandong province), which was granted to Xiao Bo or Kao Bo by King Cheng of Zhou (reigned 1042–1021  BC ). (ii) adopted as a surname by the Ku Di (庫狄) family during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (iii) traced back to other minority ethnic groups in ancient northwestern China.","Mandarin form of the Chinese surname 邸, meaning ‘official residence’ in Chinese: (i) from placename Di (邸), the name of a county (unidentified location). (ii) said to be borne by some descendants of Kujula Kadphises (called 丘就郤 or 邸就郤 in Chinese, 30–<i>c.</i> 80  AD ), founder of the Kushan Empire (one branch of the Yuezhi people originating from western China) located in Central Asia during the Eastern Han dynasty (25–220  AD )."],"variants":[{"name":"Chi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Dong, Yun, Cheng, Jae, Yong, Cheng Chung, Chi, Chun, Duk, Fang, Feng.  Korean Chung, Chong, Jae Hong, Moon, Myong, Pong, Shen, Yoo, Byung, Chang, Chol, Chong Hun.  Southeast Asian Phi, Hung, Ly, Tu, Denh, Do Van, Duong, Hao, Kieu, Mui, Nga, Phat.","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 池, meaning ‘moat’ in ancient Chinese: (i) acquired as a surname by people who lived beside a moat. (ii) from Chi (池), said to be the name of an ancient state (of unknown location and period). (iii) from the personal name Chi (池), personal name of a son of an official in the state of Qin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin and Cantonese form of the surname 遲, meaning ‘late’ in Chinese: (i) borne by descendants of Chi Ren (遲任), a person who lived during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) shortened form of the Chinese compound surname Yu-Chi (尉遲), originally the name of a tribe from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China. (iii) from the second element of the personal name Zi Chi (子遲), style name of Fan Xu, a student of Confucius (551–479  BC )."]}]},{"name":"Benevento","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Rocco, Nunzio, Antonio, Concetta, Donato, Enrico, Fiore, Luigi, Marcello, Orazio, Pasquale.","Italian:","habitational name from the city or province of Benevento in southwestern Italy."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name derived from Mapia, one of the Greek forms of Miriam. Maria is found as a male name as well as a female name. Viscount Montague, of Cowdray, Sussex, who succeeded to the title as second viscount, was christened Anthony Maria Browne. In Camden's Remains (p. 44), referred to in Delicie Literarise, occurs Thomas Maria Wingfield; and there was also a Sir Edward Maria Wingfield. The name appears to have been adopted in the latter family from Mary, daughter of Henry VIII. Compare Notes and Queries 5th S. ii. 73, 316, 478. Marie is frequently found as a male name in France and in other parts of the Continent."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maria di Benevento was born in 0993, in Italy. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Landolfo V di Benevento."},"et":{"993–":"0993–Surnud","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Surnud","0993–Female":"0993–Surnud","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Itaalia"},"fi":{"993–":"0993–Kuollut","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Kuollut","0993–Female":"0993–Kuollut","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italia"},"fr":{"993–":"0993–Décédée","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Décédée","0993–Female":"0993–Décédée","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italie","lifeSummary":"Maria di Benevento est née en 0993, à Italie. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Landolfo V di Benevento."},"de":{"993–":"0993–Verstorben","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Verstorben","0993–Female":"0993–Verstorben","993":"0993","0993":"0993","1047":"1047","0982":"0982","1010":"1010","0800":"0800","0900":"0900","Italia":"Italien","lifeSummary":"Maria di Benevento wurde 0993 in Italien geboren. Sie hatte mit Landolfo V di Benevento mindestens 1 Sohn und 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"993–":"0993–Desede","0982–1047":"0982–1047","0800–0900":"0800–0900","1010–Female":"1010–Desede","0993–F